ompanying <a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/Parent_Engagement/2014_PE_Docs/40766_Code_Guidebook_E.pdf">Guidebook</a> is intended to help in developing parent workshops on important topics as outlined in the Tool Kit. Parent Involvement Committees (PICs), School Councils and other parent groups may find this resource helpful when working with school leaders in encouraging their students to succeed, and in building positive school climates.\r\n\r\n<strong>(Parents and educators: for more information, success stories and additional resources, please visit </strong><a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/parent_engagement.html#pe2"><strong>this link</strong></a><strong>.)</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Parent Tool Kit\r\nWhat parents can do to help their child succeed in school</h3>\r\n[caption id="attachment_2364" align="alignleft" width="125"]<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ParentToolkit.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-2364" src="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ParentToolkit.png" alt="Parent Toolkit" width="125" height="179" /></a> Parent Toolkit[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis <a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/Parent_Engagement/PA%20Downloads/34918_CODE_Tool_Kit_Book-ENG_sm.pdf">Tool Kit</a> is for parents of Junior Kindergarten to Grade 12 students. Research shows that learning at home is one of the most beneficial ways to help your child succeed. This resource is intended to support parents as they help their children at home.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>(For additional resources, visit </strong><a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/parent_engagement.html#pe3"><strong>this link</strong></a><strong>.)</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Planning Parent Engagement\r\nA Guidebook for Parents and Schools</h3>\r\n[caption id="attachment_2367" align="alignnone" width="125"]<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/PlanningParentEngagement.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-2367" src="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/PlanningParentEngagement.png" alt="Planning Parent Engagement" width="125" height="162" /></a> Planning Parent Engagement[/caption]\r\n\r\nWhen we look closely at patterns of success for our students, there is ample evidence that achievement and positive school adjustment come from the support and guidance of parents and those who guide the learning and attitudes of our young people.\r\n\r\nAs school system leaders, the members of the Council of Ontario Directors of Education are very aware of the power and benefits of parent engagement. That''s why CODE is pleased to provide this <a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/Parent_Engagement/PA%20Downloads/34919_CODE_Guidebook-ENG_sm.pdf"><strong>Planning Parent Engagement Guidebook</strong></a> to accompany the Parent Tool Kit. In this Guidebook are examples of useful exercises and proven techniques for involvement and support.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>(For additional resources visit </strong><a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/parent_engagement.html#pe5"><strong>this link</strong></a><strong>.)</strong>', 'Parent engagement resources for student success', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2357-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-31 01:10:43', '2015-03-31 01:10:43', '', 2357, 'http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/2357-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
