tors.ca/Parent_Engagement/2014_PE_Docs/40766_Code_Guidebook_E.pdf">Guidebook</a> is intended to help in developing parent workshops on important topics as outlined in the Tool Kit. Parent Involvement Committees (PICs), School Councils and other parent groups may find this resource helpful when working with school leaders in encouraging their students to succeed, and in building positive school climates.\r\n\r\n<strong>(Parents and educators: for more information, success stories and additional resources, please visit </strong><a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/parent_engagement.html#pe2"><strong>this link</strong></a><strong>.)</strong>\r\n<h3>Parent Tool Kit\r\nWhat parents can do to help their child succeed in school</h3>\r\n[caption id="attachment_2364" align="alignleft" width="125"]<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ParentToolkit.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-2364" src="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/ParentToolkit.png" alt="Parent Toolkit" width="125" height="179" /></a> Parent Toolkit[/caption]\r\n\r\nThis <a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/Parent_Engagement/PA%20Downloads/34918_CODE_Tool_Kit_Book-ENG_sm.pdf">Tool Kit</a> is for parents of Junior Kindergarten to Grade 12 students. Research shows that learning at home is one of the most beneficial ways to help your child succeed. This resource is intended to support parents as they help their children at home.\r\n\r\n<strong>(For additional resources, visit </strong><a href="http://www.ontariodirectors.ca/parent_engagement.html#pe3"><strong>this link</strong></a><strong>.)</strong>\r\n<h3>Planning Parent Engagement\r\nA Guidebook for Parents and Schools</h3>\r\n[caption id="attachment_2367" align="alignleft" width="125"]<a href="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/PlanningParentEngagement.png"><img class="size-full wp-image-2367" src="http://staging.ontariosummerlearning.org/wp-content/u