(2657, 3, '2015-07-09 22:09:33', '2015-07-09 22:09:33', '"Most kids look forward to their summer vacation — and don’t even want to think about school — yet first and second graders at John N. Given Public School look excited to be there," writes Louis Pin of the Chatham Daily News. The reason? "For a fifth year, Chatham is giving young students a chance to learn over summer, and to have fun doing it. And for some, the three-week class is the only thing between them and falling far behind in school."\r\n\r\nRead the full article <a href="http://www.chathamdailynews.ca/2015/07/07/kids-given-leg-up-at-public-schools-with-lkdsb-summer-program" target="_blank">here</a>.', 'Chatham Daily News: "Kids given leg up at public schools with LKDSB summer program"', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'chatham-daily-news-kids-given-leg-up-at-public-schools-with-lkdsb-summer-program', '', '', '2015-07-10 12:39:54', '2015-07-10 12:39:54', '', 0, 'http://ontariosummerlearning.org/?p=2657', 0, 'post', '', 0),
