(2660, 3, '2015-07-10 12:59:16', '2015-07-10 12:59:16', 'Ontario''s public educational broadcaster has a new online platform, “for Ontario''s teachers, by Ontario''s teachers,” dedicated to sharing, collaboration and knowledge exchange.\r\n\r\nCreated in partnership with the Ontario Teacher''s Federation (and it''s affiliates) and the Ministry of Education, and in consultation with teachers from across the province, <a href="https://www.teachontario.ca/welcome" target="_blank">TVO''s TeachOntario</a> is designed to support teacher professional learning, foster teacher leadership, and facilitate the sharing of best practices.\r\n\r\nTeachOntario is divided into three sections:\r\n\r\n“Explore,” a publicly-accessible space that includes curated Ministry resources and research, teacher blogs, and digital resources for teachers and parents;\r\n\r\n“Share,” an educator-only space, features over 48 teacher-initiated groups focused on knowledge sharing and learning resources (e.g., 21st Century Learning and Teaching, Digital Literacy in the Classroom, Mathematics Instructional Strategies for Student Success);\r\n\r\n“Create,” a space for informal and formal collaborative and participatory online project development. (As with the “Share” space, “Create” is only accessible by Ontario educators.)\r\n\r\nThe Explore section is also home to <a href="https://www.teachontario.ca/community/explore/parents-as-partners" target="_blank">Parents as Partners</a>, a resource bank for parents of Ontario school children in kindergarten to grade 12. Here parents will find everything from age-appropriate reading lists to at-home science experiments they can do with their children using everyday household items.\r\n\r\nExplore also houses articles, videos and tip sheets to support children''s health and development.', 'TVO''s new educator platform', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2478-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-07-10 12:59:16', '2015-07-10 12:59:16', '', 2478, 'http://ontariosummerlearning.org/2478-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2662, 3, '2015-07-15 20:26:19', '2015-07-15 20:26:19', '"A new Sarnia summer camp might look a bit familiar to local kids — its cabins are classrooms, its counsellors are teachers, and its campers are also students — but this isn’t the summer school of nightmares," says Chris O''Gorman of the Sarnia Observer.  "Instead, the St. Clair Summer Learning Camp hopes campers leave after three weeks with sharper numeracy and literacy skills as well as a host of fun memories." Read the full story <a href="http://www.theobserver.ca/2015/07/09/new-sarnia-summer-camp-puts-twist-on-reading-writing-and-arithmetic" target="_blank">here</a>.', 'Sarnia Observer: "New Sarnia summer camp puts twist on reading, writing and arithmetic"', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sarnia-observer-new-sarnia-summer-camp-puts-twist-on-reading-writing-and-arithmetic', '', '', '2015-07-15 20:28:17', '2015-07-15 20:28:17', '', 0, 'http://ontariosummerlearning.org/?p=2662', 0, 'post', '', 0),
